Inner Wheel District 912 Nigeria has paid the medication and hospital bills of a cancer patient, Mrs. Aminat Ahmed, at the Federal Medical Centre (FMC), Idi-Aba, Abeokuta, Ogun State. Vice District Chairman Mrs. Funke Shinaba, who represented District Chairman Mrs. Ronke Solomon presented the donation with members and executives of the district. She said: “I am happy Inner Wheel District 912 was able to assist the Inner Wheel Club of Olumo in paying the hospital bills and medication of Aminat today. The cost of cancer care can be a heavy burden for victims and their families. From exorbitant cost of diagnosis to treatment, paying for cancer treatment can be daunting and, on its own, sickening I’m glad that the district is able to pay her bills.” 